{"rating_score": "8.0", "rating_badge": "Very good", "description": "I stay there often so the counter gives me an upgrade to a side harbor view room, that makes all the difference.", "date": "Reviewed Apr 14, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "10.0", "rating_badge": "Exceptional", "description": "I have and continue to be a big fan of Shangri-La hotels in SE Asia.  The Kowloon property, like the others that we've visited, is excellent.  It is a bit more dated and \"aged\" than some though but still very good.  What hasn't veered is the outstanding service--from our help in the Horizon Club, to the breakfast buffet and the great folks at the Concierge Desk.  Everyone is knowledgeable, eager to help, and outright friendly.  We're treated as valued family rather than mere guests.  We had a room with a Victoria Harbor view, which is wonderful both during the day and night.  It's like have a longstanding seat on the Star Ferry heading for HK Island.  The Kowloon property is near some excellent restaurants, and the East Tsim Sha Tsui subway station on the Purple Line is basically across the street from the main entrance [and a bit of a schlep via underground tunnel to the Tsim Sha Tsui subway station on the Red Line], the Star Ferry takes a modest walk, and the China Ferry to Macau is only 5 min taxi ride away.  So convenience is suberb.  Overall, it's an outstanding hotel with only minor and totally forgiveable features.", "date": "Reviewed Apr 6, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "10.0", "rating_badge": "Exceptional", "description": "The staff was always helpful and committed to getting us the right answer when approached with overall questions, about the hotel or surrounding area. Sometimes hotels treat customers differently depending on their category: business or family, for example. We didn\u2019t feel less valued as \u201cfamily\u201d customers verses \u201cbusiness.\u201d ", "date": "Reviewed Apr 3, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "2.0", "rating_badge": "Poor", "description": "It wasn\u2019t a nice experience staying with Shangri-la Kowloon. \r\nEverything that we requested for was not fulfilled \r\n1. Requested for High floors - Got the lowest you could get which was actually 7th floor. Right in plain sight of people walking along the streets which means that you either cover yourself in up in the comfort of your own room or you close the curtains which defeats the purpose of spending money for the view\r\n\r\n2. Late check out. We\u2019ve stayed in multiple 5 star hotels and we\u2019ve never been denied a late checkout pass. From 12 to 1. Wasn\u2019t expecting anything crazy like 3 hours or so. Oh and this is even after we got a late check in. We arrived at 12pm but they didn\u2019t have the room ready so we couldn\u2019t even check in at the normal time of 2pm. We were only allowed to check in at 3pm. So, an hour taken away but never returned. \r\n\r\nPoorly maintained equipment within the room. Have you ever had a mini blower in your room? Well if you\u2019ve never had it then be sure to book a stay here. The aircon was so loud. I do have a video of it but can\u2019t upload it. \r\n\r\nThere were also no electrical powerpoints by the bedside to charge your phone. So yeah make sure you put that device away from you and charge it before you tuck yourself into bed. \r\n\r\nWe didn\u2019t feel special during this stay as we did with other hotels so ill be putting my money elsewhere. ", "date": "Reviewed Mar 19, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "10.0", "rating_badge": "Exceptional", "description": "You can\u2019t go wrong with Shangrila. Hotel and service is impeccable.", "date": "Reviewed Mar 29, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "10.0", "rating_badge": "Exceptional", "description": "Central location is excellent. Price is on the high side", "date": "Reviewed Mar 26, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "10.0", "rating_badge": "Exceptional", "description": "Amazing Hotel! Amazing location! Amazing view! Very clean! Nice smell!", "date": "Reviewed Mar 26, 2019"}
{"rating_score": "8.0", "rating_badge": "Very good", "description": "Kowloon Shangri-La is a proper 5-star hotel.\r\nAs such it has a great set of amenities and offers you a pleasurable, comfortable stay.\r\n\r\nThe hotel has a grand reception area that looks very majestic. The rooms are in great condition, beautifully decorated, spacious, with big, comfortable beds and nice bathrooms. Opting in for a harbour view room is nice if you like to admire the HK skyscraper skyline across at Hong Kong island. Room service is very good and rooms are cleaned twice in a day.\r\n\r\nOverall the hotel has a lot of amenities. The fitness area and pool are small but at least they are there if you like to use them. The level of equipment is very good. \r\nThe breakfast is amongst the biggest and most varied I have encountered giving you lots of options across many different cuisines (Western, Asian etc).\r\n\r\nOn the cons side, we felt the hotel was too big and as a result overall management suffered a bit. Staff where all very professional and each individually tried their best to be helpful and accomodate the guest's needs.\r\nHowever, the reception and front desk was often getting very crowded (especially around check out times) and as a result it would take lots of time to be looked after. Similarly, at check in, you are not explained about sll offered amenities and services and associated costs or activities one can try around the city as most 5-star hotels will provide.\r\n\r\nThe breakfast area would get fairly busy and noisy and often service would be slowed down.", "date": "Reviewed Mar 13, 2019"}
